transcript.text: Welcome to own Print Shop.

In this tutorial, we'll walk you through some of the latest enhancements introduced to the Order module that are designed to simplify offline order processing, streamline the reorder flow, and improve overall admin efficiency.

With updates like quicker offline customer creation, refreshed and intuitive UI for order details, support for a few online payment methods, and the ability to reorder for a different customer using save designs, these enhancements are all about saving time and reducing manual effort.
Let's take a closer look at how each of these improvements works and how they can help you manage orders more efficiently.
We've enhanced the offline order experience to make it quicker and more user friendly.
Previously, when adding a new customer to an offline order, users had to manually fill in all the details, which we're time consuming and repetitive.
With this improvement, the process has been simplified.
Now only basic information is required to proceed.
To get started, go to Add New Order, enter the customer's e-mail address and click Next.
A pop up window will appear where you can input essential details such as store e-mail, first name and last name.
Once these fields are filled out and saved, the system will take you to the next step where shipping and billing addresses are displayed.
If the offline address settings are already enabled in the system, the default address is automatically populated, speeding up the process even further.
Simply click Next and then Save to complete the order.
In addition to the workflow improvements, we've introduced A refreshed user interface for the product page.
Now, you'll notice a much cleaner and more structured layout.
Product details are shown on the left hand side, while the artwork upload section is displayed on the right.
This provides better clarity and a more intuitive experience.
Similarly, the Payment and Shipping details section has also been updated with a cleaner new design, ensuring smoother data entry.
As part of this update, we've also added support for these five new payment methods, PayPal Advance, Stripe, POS, Razor Pay, EC Pay and E Nets.
These new methods are available under the Payment and Shipping section and further extend the flexibility of handling offline orders.
We're also excited to introduce a powerful new enhancement to the order module, Reorder for another customer with a saved design.
This feature allows admin users to easily place a reorder for either the same customer or a different one by reusing an already saved design.
It's especially helpful when a single design needs to be applied across multiple clients or internal departments, reducing the need to recreate it from scratch each time.
To use this feature, go to the order you'd like to duplicate.
From the Order Action tab, select Reorder Reprint.
This opens a new pop up window where you set the select type to Reorder.
Next, you'll be prompted to choose whether the reorder is for the same customer or another one that already exists in your admin system.
Simply enter the new customer's e-mail address in the provided field.
You'll also notice a Copy Design toggle.
If enabled, this will apply the same saved design from the original order to the new one.
If disabled, new design should be uploaded later, just like flow of upload artwork later.
Once you've made your selections, click Continue from here.
Proceed to enter the shipping and payment details and finalize the reorder.
These enhancements are part of our ongoing commitment to improve admin workflows, reduce turn around time, and enhance usability for order processing.
Stay tuned for more updates.
And as always, if you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chatononprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
